  <div class="explainer" role="region" aria-label="What is lipa mdogo mdogo in Kenya">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="explainer-inner">
        <h2 class="explainer-h2">What is Lipa Mdogo Mdogo in Kenya?</h2>
        <p class="explainer-p">Lipa mdogo mdogo — Swahili for "pay a little by little" — is Kenya's most popular way to own a smartphone without paying the full price upfront. Instead of buying outright, you place a small deposit via M-Pesa and clear the remaining balance over weekly or monthly instalments. At MdogomdogoDeals, deposits start from as little as KSh 2,000, and repayment plans run over 3 or 6 months depending on the phone you choose. No bank account, no CRB check, and no guarantor is ever required.</p>
        <!-- ── SEO: Lipa pole pole coverage ── -->
        <p class="explainer-p">You may also hear this called <strong>lipa pole pole</strong> — it means exactly the same thing: pay gradually, at your own pace. Both terms are used interchangeably across Nairobi, and both describe the same flexible instalment plan available here.</p>
        <p class="explainer-p">To qualify, you only need a working M-Pesa number and your initial deposit. Once paid, the phone is yours to keep and use immediately — instalments continue in the background on whatever schedule suits you best: daily, weekly, or monthly. This model has become especially popular in Nairobi, Kiambu, Machakos, and Kajiado, where many working Kenyans prefer to spread the cost of a quality device without dipping into savings or taking out a loan.</p>
        <p class="explainer-p">Every phone on this site is 100% brand new, factory sealed, and sourced from authorized Kenyan distributors — meaning you get the full manufacturer warranty alongside the convenience of flexible payments. We deliver free, the same day, anywhere in Greater Nairobi when you order before 2 PM.</p>
      </div>
